In [3]:
def finput(x,w):
    return np.exp(-(x)**2/(w)**2)*np.sqrt(2/(np.pi*w))

def Hfree(kx,d):
    hfreeexp=d*np.sqrt(k**2-kx**2+0j)
    hfree=np.exp(+1j*hfreeexp)
    return hfree

def Tlens(x,f):
    tlensexp=np.pi*x**2/(wl*f)
    tlens=np.exp(-1j*tlensexp)
    return tlens

def Ulens(datain,x,f):
    output=np.multiply(datain,Tlens(x,f))
    return output

def Ulensf(datain,x):
    ulensf=np.fft.fft(datain)
    freq=np.fft.fftfreq(datain.shape[-1])*len(x)*2*np.pi/(max(x)-min(x))
    return freq,ulensf

def Ulensfd(xdata,kx,d):
    ulensfd=np.multiply(xdata,Hfree(kx,d))
    return ulensfd

def Ulensd(data):
    return np.fft.ifft(data)

Calculations, hybrid method¶

At first, the beam path will be calculated using fourier optics, then the 2d intensity will be calculated analytically.

def displacedgaussian(x,b,c):
    return np.exp(-(x-c)**2/b**2)*np.sqrt(2/(np.pi*b))

def calculate(offset,f,win,peachbeam,plot):
    
    """
    offset: offset of beams from centre of lens
    f: focal distance
    win: input waist radius
    with new fitting method
    """
    #input 
    xmin=-0.05
    xmax=0.05
    xres=0.0000001
    x=np.linspace(xmin,xmax,int((xmax-xmin)/xres))
    input0=np.sqrt(peachbeam)*finput(x-offset,win)
    #norm=np.sum((abs(input0))**2)*xres
    lensoutput=Ulens(input0,x,f)
    freq,flensoutput=Ulensf(lensoutput,x)
    #z
    zmin=0
    zmax=1.1*f
    zres=0.0005
    z=np.linspace(zmin,zmax,int((zmax-zmin)/zres))
    #do the calcullations
    #prepare fitting
    waistvalues=np.zeros(len(z))
    offsets=np.zeros(len(z))
    waistxloc=[]
    approxangle=np.arctan(offset/f)
    approxw0=(wl*f/(np.pi*win))*(1+(wl*f/(np.pi*win**2))**2)**-0.5
    approxbeamdiv=wl/(np.pi*approxw0)
    b0=win
    c0=offset
    xfitmax=int((abs(offset)+3*win)/xres)
    #loop
    if plot==True:
        data=np.zeros((len(z),len(x)),dtype=np.complex_)
        for i in (range(len(z))):
            afterz=Ulensfd(flensoutput,freq,z[i])
            data[i,:]=np.fft.ifft(afterz)
            dc=zres*np.tan(approxangle)*4 #factor of 4 is for safety
            db=zres*np.tan(approxbeamdiv)*4 #factor 4 is for safety
            popt,pcov=curve_fit(displacedgaussian,x[int(len(x)/2)-xfitmax:int(len(x)/2)+xfitmax],abs(data[i,int(len(x)/2)-xfitmax:int(len(x)/2)+xfitmax]),p0=[b0,c0],bounds=[[b0-db,c0-dc],[b0+db,c0+dc]])
            waistvalues[i]=popt[0]*10**6
            offsets[i]=popt[1]
            #a0=popt[0]
            b0=popt[0]
            c0=popt[1]
        #plotting
        plt.figure()
        plt.imshow((abs(data))**2,aspect="auto",origin='lower',extent=[xmin,xmax,zmin,zmax])
        plt.xlim(-0.002,0.002)
        plt.show()     
        #finding angle
        waistlocation=np.unravel_index((abs(data)).argmax(),(abs(data)).shape)
        waistxlocation=waistlocation[1]*xres+xmin
        waistzlocation=waistlocation[0]*zres+zmin
        dx=offset-waistxlocation
        dz=waistzlocation-zmin
        angle=np.arctan(dx/dz)*180/np.pi
    else:
        rsq=np.zeros(len(z))
        for i in tqdm_notebook(range(len(z))):
            afterz=Ulensfd(flensoutput,freq,z[i])
            tempdata=np.fft.ifft(afterz)
            dc=zres*np.tan(approxangle)*2 #factor of 2 is for safety
            db=zres*np.tan(approxbeamdiv)*2 #factor 2 is for safety
            xdata=x[int(len(x)/2)-xfitmax:int(len(x)/2)+xfitmax]
            ydata=abs(tempdata[int(len(x)/2)-xfitmax:int(len(x)/2)+xfitmax])
            popt,pcov=curve_fit(displacedgaussian,xdata,ydata,p0=[b0,c0],bounds=[[b0-db,c0-dc],[b0+db,c0+dc]])
            residuals=abs(ydata)-displacedgaussian(xdata,*popt)
            ss_res=np.sum(residuals**2)
            ss_tot=np.sum((ydata-np.mean(ydata))**2)
            r_squared=1-(ss_res / ss_tot)
            rsq[i]=1-r_squared
            if r_squared<0.9999:
                print("BAD FITTING")
            waistvalues[i]=popt[0]*10**6
            offsets[i]=popt[1]
            b0=popt[0]
            c0=popt[1]
            waistxloc.append(popt[1])
        waistzlocation=np.argmin(waistvalues)*zres+zmin
        waistxlocation=np.array(waistxloc)[np.argmin(waistvalues)]
        dx=offset-waistxlocation
        dz=waistzlocation
        angle=np.arctan(dx/dz)*180/np.pi
    plt.figure()
    plt.plot(z,waistvalues*np.cos(angle*np.pi/180))
    plt.title("b0")
    plt.show()
    plt.figure()
    plt.plot(z,offsets)
    plt.title("c0")
    plt.show()
    plt.figure()
    plt.plot(z,rsq)
    plt.title("1-rsq")
    plt.show()
    w0=np.min(waistvalues*np.cos(angle*np.pi/180))*10**-6
    rotwdist=waistzlocation/np.cos(angle*np.pi/180)
    astigm=rotwdist-offset/np.sin(angle*np.pi/180)
    return angle, w0, astigm, rsq

def calculate2(offset,f,win,peachbeam,plot):
    
    """
    offset: offset of beams from centre of lens
    f: focal distance
    win: input waist radius
    peachbeam: beam power, here it does not matter
    plot: if true, imshow, if false no imshow
    The function returns
    angle: angle of beam in degrees
    w0: waist radius of beam
    astigm: astigmatism,negative means the focus is too early
    rsq: rsquared values
    with new fitting method
    """
    #input 
    xmin=-0.05
    xmax=0.05
    xres=0.00000005
    x=np.linspace(xmin,xmax,int((xmax-xmin)/xres))
    input0=np.sqrt(peachbeam)*finput(x-offset,win)
    #norm=np.sum((abs(input0))**2)*xres
    lensoutput=Ulens(input0,x,f)
    freq,flensoutput=Ulensf(lensoutput,x)
    #z
    zmin=0.85*f
    zmax=1.05*f
    zres=0.0005
    z=np.linspace(zmin,zmax,int((zmax-zmin)/zres))
    #do the calcullations
    #prepare fitting
    waistvalues=np.zeros(len(z))
    offsets=np.zeros(len(z))
    b0lowerbound=np.zeros(len(z))
    b0upperbound=np.zeros(len(z))
    c0lowerbound=np.zeros(len(z))
    c0upperbound=np.zeros(len(z))
    waistxloc=[]
    approxangle=np.arctan(offset/f)
    approxw0=(wl*f/(np.pi*win))*(1+(wl*f/(np.pi*win**2))**2)**-0.5
    approxz0=np.pi*approxw0**2/wl
    z0beforelens=np.pi*win**2/wl
    approxbeamdiv=wl/(np.pi*approxw0)
    approxfocdist=f/(1+(f/z0beforelens)**2)
    print(approxfocdist)
    b0=np.sqrt(approxw0**2*(1+(approxfocdist-zmin)**2/approxz0**2))
    c0=offset-zmin*np.tan(approxangle)
    xfitmax=int((abs(offset)+3*win)/xres)

    #loop
    if plot==True:
        data=np.zeros((len(z),len(x)),dtype=np.complex_)
        for i in (range(len(z))):
            afterz=Ulensfd(flensoutput,freq,z[i])
            data[i,:]=np.fft.ifft(afterz)
            dc=zres*np.tan(approxangle)*6 #factor of 4 is for safety
            db=zres*np.tan(approxbeamdiv)*6 #factor 4 is for safety
            popt,pcov=curve_fit(displacedgaussian,x[int(len(x)/2)-xfitmax:int(len(x)/2)+xfitmax],abs(data[i,int(len(x)/2)-xfitmax:int(len(x)/2)+xfitmax]),p0=[b0,c0],bounds=[[b0-db,c0-dc],[b0+db,c0+dc]])
            waistvalues[i]=popt[0]*10**6
            offsets[i]=popt[1]
            #a0=popt[0]
            b0=popt[0]
            c0=popt[1]
        #plotting
        plt.figure()
        plt.imshow((abs(data))**2,aspect="auto",origin='lower',extent=[xmin,xmax,zmin,zmax])
        plt.xlim(-0.002,0.002)
        plt.show()     
        #finding angle
        waistlocation=np.unravel_index((abs(data)).argmax(),(abs(data)).shape)
        waistxlocation=waistlocation[1]*xres+xmin
        waistzlocation=waistlocation[0]*zres+zmin
        dx=offset-waistxlocation
        dz=waistzlocation-zmin
        angle=np.arctan(dx/dz)*180/np.pi
    else:
        rsq=np.zeros(len(z))
        for i in tqdm_notebook(range(len(z))):
            afterz=Ulensfd(flensoutput,freq,z[i])
            tempdata=np.fft.ifft(afterz)
            dc=zres*np.tan(approxangle)*8 #factor of 2 is for safety, changed to 8 because of bad fitting
            db=zres*np.tan(approxbeamdiv)*8 #factor 2 is for safety, changed to 8 because of bad fitting
            b0lowerbound[i]=(b0-db)*10**6
            b0upperbound[i]=(b0+db)*10**6
            c0lowerbound[i]=(c0-dc)
            c0upperbound[i]=(c0+dc)
            #print(b0+db)
            #print(b0-db)
            xdata=x[int(len(x)/2)-xfitmax:int(len(x)/2)+xfitmax]
            ydata=abs(tempdata[int(len(x)/2)-xfitmax:int(len(x)/2)+xfitmax])
            popt,pcov=curve_fit(displacedgaussian,xdata,ydata,p0=[b0,c0],bounds=[[b0-db,c0-dc],[b0+db,c0+dc]])
            residuals=abs(ydata)-displacedgaussian(xdata,*popt)
            ss_res=np.sum(residuals**2)
            ss_tot=np.sum((ydata-np.mean(ydata))**2)
            r_squared=1-(ss_res / ss_tot)
            rsq[i]=1-r_squared
            if r_squared<0.99999:
                print("BAD FITTING")
            waistvalues[i]=popt[0]*10**6
            offsets[i]=popt[1]
            b0=popt[0]
            c0=popt[1]
            #print(b0)
            waistxloc.append(popt[1])
            #check if plot is fine
            #plt.figure()
            #plt.plot(xdata,ydata)
            #plt.plot(xdata,displacedgaussian(xdata,*popt))
            #plt.xlim(-0.001,0.001)
            #plt.show()
        waistzlocation=np.argmin(waistvalues)*zres+zmin
        waistxlocation=np.array(waistxloc)[np.argmin(waistvalues)]
        #print(waistzlocation)
        #print(waistxlocation)
        dx=offset-waistxlocation
        dz=waistzlocation
        angle=np.arctan(dx/dz)*180/np.pi
    plt.figure()
    plt.plot(z,waistvalues*np.cos(angle*np.pi/180),label='b0')
    plt.plot(z,b0lowerbound*np.cos(angle*np.pi/180),label="b0 lower bound")
    plt.plot(z,b0upperbound*np.cos(angle*np.pi/180),label="b0 upper bound")
    plt.title("b0")
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    plt.show()
    plt.figure()
    plt.plot(z,offsets)
    plt.plot(z,c0lowerbound,label="c0 lower bound")
    plt.plot(z,c0upperbound,label="c0 upper bound")
    plt.title("c0")
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    plt.show()
    plt.figure()
    plt.plot(z,rsq)
    plt.title("1-rsq")
    plt.show()
    w0=np.min(waistvalues*np.cos(angle*np.pi/180))*10**-6
    rotwdist=waistzlocation/np.cos(angle*np.pi/180)
    astigm=rotwdist-offset/np.sin(angle*np.pi/180) #negative astigm means the waist is too early
    return angle, w0, astigm, rsq

#stuff for beams
def wx(z,w0x):
    """
    Input: 
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w0x: waist radius along the x direction [m]
    Output: waist radius along the x direction at position z from the waist [m]
    """
    return w0x*np.sqrt(1+(wl*z/(np.pi*w0x**2))**2)

def wy(z,w0y):
    """
    Input: 
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w0y: waist radius along the y direction [m]
    Output: waist radius along the y direction at position z from the waist [m]
    """
    return w0y*np.sqrt(1+(wl*z/(np.pi*w0y**2))**2)

def Rxrec(z,w0x):
    """
    Input:
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w0x: waist radius along the x direction [m]
    Output: Reciprocal radius of curvature along the x direction at position z from the waist [1/m]
    """
    if z==0:
        rx=0
    else: 
        rx=(z+(1/z)*(np.pi*w0x**2/wl)**2)**-1
    return rx

def Ryrec(z,w0y):
    """
    Input:
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w0y: waist radius along the y direction [m]
    Output: Reciprocal radius of curvature along the y direction at position z from the waist [1/m]
    """
    if z==0:
        ry=0
    else: 
        ry=(z+(1/z)*(np.pi*w0y**2/wl)**2)**-1
    return ry

def phix(z,w0x):
    """
    Input:
    -z: distance along the z axis [m]
    -w0x: waist radius along the x direction [m]
    Output: Phase shift when propagating along z direction due to the x direction [dimensionless]
    """
    return np.arctan(wl*z/(np.pi*w0x**2))

def phiy(z,w0y):
    """    
    Input:
    -z: distance along the z axis [m]
    -w0y: waist radius along the y direction [m]
    Output: Phase shift when propagating along z direction due to the y direction [dimensionless]
    """
    return np.arctan(wl*z/(np.pi*w0y**2))

def Efield(x,y,z,w0x,w0y):
    """
    Input: 
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w0x: waist radius along the x direction [m]
    -w0y: waist radius along the y direction [m]
    Output: Complex electric field amplitude of a gaussian beam at position r=(x,y,z) with waist radii (w0x,w0y)
    [normalised to give unity power]
    """
    norm=(2/(np.pi*wx(z,w0x)*wy(z,w0y)))**0.5
    real=-x**2/(wx(z,w0x))**2-y**2/(wy(z,w0y))**2
    phase=-(np.pi*Rxrec(z,w0x)*x**2/wl)-(np.pi*Ryrec(z,w0y)*y**2/wl)+(phix(z,w0x)/2)+(phiy(z,w0y)/2)
    efield=norm*np.exp(complex(real,phase))
    return efield


#Coordinate transformation by rotation matrices 

def Rx(theta):
    """
    Input: angle of rotation [rad]
    Output: rotation matrix for rotation about the x axis [dimensionless]
    """
    rx=np.array([[1,0,0],[0,np.cos(theta),-np.sin(theta)],[0,np.sin(theta),np.cos(theta)]])
    return rx

def Ry(theta):
    """
    Input: angle of rotation [rad]
    Output: rotation matrix for rotation about the y axis [dimensionless]
    """
    ry=np.array([[np.cos(theta),0,-np.sin(theta)],[0,1,0],[np.sin(theta),0,np.cos(theta)]])
    return ry

def Rz(theta):
    """
    Input: angle of rotation [rad]
    Output: rotation matrix for rotation about the z axis [dimensionless]
    """
    rz=np.array([[np.cos(theta),-np.sin(theta),0],[np.sin(theta),np.cos(theta),0],[0,0,1]])
    return rz

def R(alpha,beta,gamma):
    """
    Input: 
    -alpha: angle of rotation about the x axis [rad] 
    -beta: angle of rotation about the y axis [rad]
    -gamma: angle of rotation about the z axis [rad]
    Output: rotation matrix for rotation about all 3 axes [dimensionless]
    """
    r=Rx(alpha)@Ry(beta)@Rz(gamma)
    return r

def newx(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z):
    """
    Input: 
    -alpha: angle of rotation about the x axis [rad]
    -beta: angle of rotation about the y axis [rad]
    -gamma: angle of rotation about the z axis [rad]
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    Output: x coordinate of rotated position [m]
    """
    r=np.array([x,y,z])
    xhat=np.array([1,0,0])
    return (R(alpha,beta,gamma)@r)@xhat

def newy(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z):
    """
    Input: 
    -alpha: angle of rotation about the x axis [rad]
    -beta: angle of rotation about the y axis [rad]
    -gamma: angle of rotation about the z axis [rad]
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    Output: y coordinate of rotated position [m]
    """
    r=np.array([x,y,z])
    yhat=np.array([0,1,0])
    return (R(alpha,beta,gamma)@r)@yhat

def newz(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z):
    """
    Input: 
    -alpha: angle of rotation about the x axis [rad]
    -beta: angle of rotation about the y axis [rad]
    -gamma: angle of rotation about the z axis [rad]
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    Output: z coordinate of rotated position [m]
    """
    r=np.array([x,y,z])
    zhat=np.array([0,0,1])
    return (R(alpha,beta,gamma)@r)@zhat

def newx(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z):
    nx=x*np.cos(beta)*np.cos(gamma)-z*np.sin(beta)-y*np.cos(beta)*np.sin(gamma)
    return nx


def newz(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z):
    nz=z*np.cos(alpha)*np.cos(beta)+x*(np.cos(alpha)*np.cos(gamma)*np.sin(beta)+np.sin(alpha)*np.sin(gamma))+y*(np.cos(gamma)*np.sin(alpha)-np.cos(alpha)*np.sin(beta)*np.sin(gamma))
    return nz

def newy(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z):
    ny=-z*np.cos(beta)*np.sin(alpha)+x*(-np.cos(gamma)*np.sin(alpha)*np.sin(beta)+np.cos(alpha)*np.sin(gamma))+y*(np.cos(alpha)*np.cos(gamma)+np.sin(alpha)*np.sin(beta)*np.sin(gamma))
    return ny


#rotated gaussian beam definitions

def wxr(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z,w0x):
    """
    Input:
    -alpha: angle of rotation about the x axis [rad]
    -beta: angle of rotation about the y axis [rad]
    -gamma: angle of rotation about the z axis [rad]
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w0x: waist radius along the x direction [m]
    Output: waist radius of the rotated beam at position r=(x,y,z) along the x direction [m]
    """
    return wx(newz(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z),w0x)

def wyr(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z,w0y):
    """
    Input:
    -alpha: angle of rotation about the x axis [rad]
    -beta: angle of rotation about the y axis [rad]
    -gamma: angle of rotation about the z axis [rad]
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w0y: waist radius along the y direction [m]
    Output: waist radius of the rotated beam at position r=(x,y,z) along the y direction [m]
    """
    return wy(newz(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z),w0y)

def Rxrecr(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z,w0x):
    """
    Input:
    -alpha: angle of rotation about the x axis [rad]
    -beta: angle of rotation about the y axis [rad]
    -gamma: angle of rotation about the z axis [rad]
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w0x: waist radius along the x direction [m]
    Output: Reciprocal radius of curvature of the the rotated beam at position r=(x,y,z) along the x direction [m]
    """
    if newz(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z)==0:
        rx=0
    else: 
        rx=(newz(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z)+(1/newz(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z))*(np.pi*w0x**2/wl)**2)**-1
    return rx

def Ryrecr(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z,w0y):
    """
    Input:
    -alpha: angle of rotation about the x axis [rad]
    -beta: angle of rotation about the y axis [rad]
    -gamma: angle of rotation about the z axis [rad]
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w0y: waist radius along the y direction [m]
    Output: Reciprocal radius of curvature of the the rotated beam at position r=(x,y,z) along the y direction [m]
    """
    if newz(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z)==0:
        ry=0
    else: 
        ry=(newz(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z)+(1/newz(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z))*(np.pi*w0y**2/wl)**2)**-1
    return ry

def Rxrecr(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z,w0x):
    """
    Input:
    -alpha: angle of rotation about the x axis [rad]
    -beta: angle of rotation about the y axis [rad]
    -gamma: angle of rotation about the z axis [rad]
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w0x: waist radius along the x direction [m]
    Output: Reciprocal radius of curvature of the the rotated beam at position r=(x,y,z) along the x direction [m]
    """
    rx=(newz(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z)+np.divide(1,newz(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z))*(np.pi*w0x**2/wl)**2)**-1
    return rx

def Ryrecr(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z,w0y):
    """
    Input:
    -alpha: angle of rotation about the x axis [rad]
    -beta: angle of rotation about the y axis [rad]
    -gamma: angle of rotation about the z axis [rad]
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w0y: waist radius along the y direction [m]
    Output: Reciprocal radius of curvature of the the rotated beam at position r=(x,y,z) along the y direction [m]
    """
    ry=(newz(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z)+np.divide(1,newz(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z))*(np.pi*w0y**2/wl)**2)**-1
    return ry

def phixr(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z,w0x):
    """
    Input
    -alpha: angle of rotation about the x axis [rad]
    -beta: angle of rotation about the y axis [rad]
    -gamma: angle of rotation about the z axis [rad]
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w0x: waist radius along the x direction [m]
    Output: Phase shift when propagating along rotated z direction due to the new x direction [dimensionless] 
    """
    return np.arctan(wl*newz(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z)/(np.pi*w0x**2))

def phiyr(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z,w0y):
    """
    Input:
    -alpha: angle of rotation about the x axis [rad]
    -beta: angle of rotation about the y axis [rad]
    -gamma: angle of rotation about the z axis [rad]
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w0y: waist radius along the y direction [m]
    Output: Phase shift when propagating along rotated z direction due to the new x direction [dimensionless] 
    """
    return np.arctan(wl*newz(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z)/(np.pi*w0y**2))

def Efieldr(x,y,z,w0x,w0y,alpha,beta,gamma):
    """
    Input:
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w0x: waist radius along the x direction [m]
    -w0y: waist radius along the y direction [m]
    -alpha: angle of rotation about the x axis [rad]
    -beta: angle of rotation about the y axis [rad]
    -gamma: angle of rotation about the z axis [rad]
    Output: Complex electric field amplitude of a rotated gaussian beam at position r=(x,y,z) with waist radii (w0x,w0y) [normalised to give unity power]
    """
    norm=(2/(np.pi*wxr(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z,w0x)*wyr(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z,w0y)))**0.5
    real=-(newx(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z))**2/(wxr(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z,w0x))**2-(newy(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z))**2/(wyr(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z,w0y))**2
    phase=-(np.pi*Rxrecr(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z,w0x)*(newx(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z))**2/wl)-(np.pi*Ryrecr(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z,w0y)*(newy(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z))**2/wl)+(phixr(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z,w0x)/2)+(phiyr(alpha,beta,gamma,x,y,z,w0y)/2)
    efield=norm*np.exp(real+1j*phase)
    return efield

def Efieldrot(x,y,z,w0x,w0y,kx,ky,kz):
    """
    Input:
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w0x: waist radius along the x direction [m]
    -w0y: waist radius along the y direction [m]
    -kx: x component of wave vector [1/m]
    -ky: y component of wave vector [1/m]
    -kz: z component of wave vector [1/m]
    Output: Complex electric field amplitude of a rotated gaussian beam at position r=(x,y,z)
    with waist radii (w0x,w0y) including the spatial propagation phase factor [normalised to give unity power]
    """
    efieldrot=Efieldr(x,y,z,w0x,w0y,np.arctan(ky/kz),np.arctan(kx/kz),0)*np.exp(1j*(kx*x+ky*y+kz*z))
    return efieldrot

def Introt(x,y,z,w0x,w0y,kx,ky,kz):
    """
    Input:
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w0x: waist radius along the x direction [m]
    -w0y: waist radius along the y direction [m]
    -kx: x component of wave vector [1/m]
    -ky: y component of wave vector [1/m]
    -kz: z component of wave vector [1/m]
    Output: Intensity of a rotated gaussian beam at position r=(x,y,z), with waist radii (w0x,w0y) [W/m^2]
    """
    introt=Efieldrot(x,y,z,w0x,w0y,kx,ky,kz)*np.conj(Efieldrot(x,y,z,w0x,w0y,kx,ky,kz))
    return introt.real

def E1gens(x,y,z,w1,w2,theta):
    """
    Input:
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w1: waist radius along the x direction [m]
    -w2: waist radius along the y direction [m]
    -theta: angle between rotated beam and beam going along the z direction [degrees]
    Output: Electric field vector of a rotated gaussian beam to the right compared to a beam going in the z direction
    at position r=(x,y,z), with waist radii (w1,22) [normalised to give unity power]
    """
    ex=0
    ey=Efieldrot(x,y,z,w1,w2,np.sin(theta*np.pi/180)*2*np.pi/wl,0,np.cos(theta*np.pi/180)*2*np.pi/wl)
    ez=0
    return np.array([ex,ey,ez])

def E2gens(x,y,z,w1,w2,theta):
    """
    Input:
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w1: waist radius along the x direction [m]
    -w2: waist radius along the y direction [m]
    -theta: angle between rotated beam and beam going along the z direction [degrees]
    Output: Electric field vector of a rotated gaussian beam to the left compared to a beam going in the z direction
    at position r=(x,y,z), with waist radii (w1,w2) [normalised to give unity power]
    """
    ex=0
    ey=Efieldrot(x,y,z,w1,w2,np.sin(-theta*np.pi/180)*2*np.pi/wl,0,np.cos(-theta*np.pi/180)*2*np.pi/wl)
    ez=0
    return np.array([ex,ey,ez])

def E1gens(x,y,z,w1,w2,theta):
    """
    Input:
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w1: waist radius along the x direction [m]
    -w2: waist radius along the y direction [m]
    -theta: angle between rotated beam and beam going along the z direction [degrees]
    Output: Electric field vector of a rotated gaussian beam to the right compared to a beam going in the z direction
    at position r=(x,y,z), with waist radii (w1,22) [normalised to give unity power]
    """
    ex=0
    ey=Efieldrot(x,y,z,w1,w2,np.sin(theta*np.pi/180)*2*np.pi/wl,0,np.cos(theta*np.pi/180)*2*np.pi/wl)
    ez=0
    return ey

def E2gens(x,y,z,w1,w2,theta):
    """
    Input:
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w1: waist radius along the x direction [m]
    -w2: waist radius along the y direction [m]
    -theta: angle between rotated beam and beam going along the z direction [degrees]
    Output: Electric field vector of a rotated gaussian beam to the left compared to a beam going in the z direction
    at position r=(x,y,z), with waist radii (w1,w2) [normalised to give unity power]
    """
    ex=0
    ey=Efieldrot(x,y,z,w1,w2,np.sin(-theta*np.pi/180)*2*np.pi/wl,0,np.cos(-theta*np.pi/180)*2*np.pi/wl)
    ez=0
    return ey
                 
def Egens(x,y,z,w1x,w1y,w2x,w2y,theta,peachbeam):
    """
    Input:
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w1x: waist radius along the x direction, first beam [m]
    -w1y: waist radius along the y direction, first beam [m]
    -w2x: waist radius along the x direction, second beam [m]
    -w2y: waist radius along the y direction, second beam [m]
    -theta: angle between rotated beam and beam going along the z direction. Here, it is half of the angle
    between the two beams[degrees]
    -peachbeam: power of each of these beams [W]
    Output: Electric field vector of two rotated gaussian beams left and right compared to a beam going in the z direction
    at position r=(x,y,z), with waist radii (w1,w2) [normalised to give unity power]
    """
    egens=np.sqrt(peachbeam)*E1gens(x,y,z,w1x,w1y,theta)+np.sqrt(peachbeam)*E2gens(x,y,z,w2x,w2y,theta)
    return egens

def Egensnew(x,y,z,w1x,w1y,w2x,w2y,theta,astigm,peachbeam):
    """
    Input:
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w1x: waist radius along the x direction, first beam [m]
    -w1y: waist radius along the y direction, first beam [m]
    -w2x: waist radius along the x direction, second beam [m]
    -w2y: waist radius along the y direction, second beam [m]
    -theta: angle between rotated beam and beam going along the z direction. Here, it is half of the angle
    between the two beams[degrees]
    -astigm: astigmatism 
    -peachbeam: power of each of these beams [W]
    Output: Electric field vector of two rotated gaussian beams left and right compared to a beam going in the z direction
    at position r=(x,y,z), with waist radii (w1,w2), including astigmatism [normalised to give unity power]
    """    
    egens=np.sqrt(peachbeam)*E1gens(x+astigm*np.sin(theta*np.pi/180),y,z+astigm*np.cos(theta*np.pi/180),w1x,w1y,theta)+np.sqrt(peachbeam)*E2gens(x-astigm*np.sin(theta*np.pi/180),y,z+astigm*np.cos(theta*np.pi/180),w2x,w2y,theta)
    return egens

def Egensnew2(x,y,z,w1x,w1y,w2x,w2y,theta,astigm,peachbeam):
    """
    Input:
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w1x: waist radius along the x direction, first beam [m]
    -w1y: waist radius along the y direction, first beam [m]
    -w2x: waist radius along the x direction, second beam [m]
    -w2y: waist radius along the y direction, second beam [m]
    -theta: angle between rotated beam and beam going along the z direction. Here, it is half of the angle
    between the two beams[degrees]
    -astigm: astigmatism 
    -peachbeam: power of each of these beams [W]
    Output: Electric field vector of two rotated gaussian beams left and right compared to a beam going in the z direction
    at position r=(x,y,z), with waist radii (w1,w2), including astigmatism [normalised to give unity power]
    """    
    egens=np.sqrt(peachbeam)*E1gens(x+astigm*np.sin(theta*np.pi/180),y,z+astigm*np.cos(theta*np.pi/180),w1x,w1y,theta)
    return egens


def Intgens(x,y,z,w1x,w1y,w2x,w2y,theta,peachbeam):
    """
    Input:
    -x: position along the x axis [m]
    -y: position along the y axis [m]
    -z: position along the z axis [m]
    -w1x: waist radius along the x direction, first beam [m]
    -w1y: waist radius along the y direction, first beam [m]
    -w2x: waist radius along the x direction, second beam [m]
    -w2y: waist radius along the y direction, second beam [m]
    -theta: angle between rotated beam and beam going along the z direction. Here, it is half of the angle
    between the two beams[degrees]
    -peachbeam: power of each of these beams [W]
    Output: Intensity of two rotated gaussian beams left and right compared to a beam going in the z direction
    at position r=(x,y,z), with waist radii (w1,w2) [W/m^2]
    """
    intgens=Egens(x,y,z,w1x,w1y,w2x,w2y,theta,peachbeam)*np.conj(Egens(x,y,z,w1x,w1y,w2x,w2y,theta,peachbeam))
    return intgens.real

def Intgensnew(x,y,z,w1x,w1y,w2x,w2y,theta,astigm,peachbeam):
    """
    Input:

    -y: position along the y axis [m]

    return intgens.real

def hybridcalculate(offset,f,win,peachbeam,xlim,ylim,zlim):
    angle,w0,astigm,rsq=calculate(offset,f,win,1,False) #changed from calculate2 to calculate 
    print(angle)
    print(w0)
    print(astigm)
    xmin=-xlim*10**-6
    xmax=xlim*10**-6
    xres=0.2e-6
    ymin=-ylim*10**-6
    ymax=ylim*10**-6
    yres=0.2e-6    
    zmin=-zlim*10**-6
    zmax=zlim*10**-6
    zres=0.2e-6
    x=np.linspace(xmin,xmax,int((xmax-xmin)/xres))
    y=np.linspace(ymin,ymax,int((ymax-ymin)/yres))
    z=np.linspace(zmin,zmax,int((zmax-zmin)/zres))
    data=np.zeros((len(z),len(x)))
    for i in tqdm_notebook(range(len(z))):
        data[i,:]=Intgensnew(x,0,z[i],w0,w0,w0,w0,angle,astigm,peachbeam)
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,6))
    plt.imshow(data,aspect="auto",extent=[-xlim,xlim,-zlim,zlim])  
    plt.xlabel("x [$\mu m$]")
    plt.ylabel("z [$\mu m$]")
    plt.show()
    data1=np.zeros((len(y),len(x)))
    for i in tqdm_notebook(range(len(y))):
        data1[i,:]=Intgensnew(x,y[i],0,w0,w0,w0,w0,angle,astigm,peachbeam)
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,6))
    plt.imshow(data1,aspect="auto",extent=[-xlim,xlim,-ylim,ylim])   
    plt.xlabel("x [$\mu m$]")
    plt.ylabel("y [$\mu m$]")
    plt.show()
    data2=np.zeros((len(z),len(y)))
    for i in tqdm_notebook(range(len(z))):
        data2[i,:]=Intgensnew(0,y,z[i],w0,w0,w0,w0,angle,astigm,peachbeam)
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,6))
    plt.imshow(data2,aspect="auto",extent=[-ylim,ylim,-zlim,zlim]) 
    plt.xlabel("y [$\mu m$]")
    plt.ylabel("z [$\mu m$]")
    plt.show()
    plt.figure()
    plt.plot(x,data[int(len(z)/2),:]*1.47e-8)
    plt.ylabel("Optical dipole potential [Erec]")
    plt.show()
    return data,data1,data2,x,y,z

def hybridcalculatetaglens(offset,f,win,peachbeam,xlim,ylim,zlim):
    angle,w0,astigm,rsq=calculate2(offset,f,win,1,False)
    print(angle)
    print(w0)
    print(astigm)
    xmin=-xlim*10**-6
    xmax=xlim*10**-6
    xres=0.2e-6
    ymin=-ylim*10**-6
    ymax=ylim*10**-6
    yres=0.2e-6    
    zmin=-zlim*10**-6
    zmax=zlim*10**-6
    zres=0.2e-6
    x=np.linspace(xmin,xmax,int((xmax-xmin)/xres))
    y=np.linspace(ymin,ymax,int((ymax-ymin)/yres))
    z=np.linspace(zmin,zmax,int((zmax-zmin)/zres))
    data=np.zeros((len(z),len(x)))
    for i in tqdm_notebook(range(len(z))):
        data[i,:]=Intgensnew(x,0,z[i]-(offset/np.tan(angle))+0.2,w0,w0,w0,w0,angle,astigm,peachbeam)
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,6))
    plt.imshow(data,aspect="auto",extent=[-xlim,xlim,-zlim,zlim])  
    plt.xlabel("x [$\mu m$]")
    plt.ylabel("z [$\mu m$]")
    plt.show()
    data1=np.zeros((len(y),len(x)))
    for i in tqdm_notebook(range(len(y))):
        data1[i,:]=Intgensnew(x,y[i],-(offset/np.tan(angle))+0.2,w0,w0,w0,w0,angle,astigm,peachbeam)
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,6))
    plt.imshow(data1,aspect="auto",extent=[-xlim,xlim,-ylim,ylim])   
    plt.xlabel("x [$\mu m$]")
    plt.ylabel("y [$\mu m$]")
    plt.show()
    data2=np.zeros((len(z),len(y)))
    for i in tqdm_notebook(range(len(z))):
        data2[i,:]=Intgensnew(0,y,z[i]-(offset/np.tan(angle))+0.2,w0,w0,w0,w0,angle,astigm,peachbeam)
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,6))
    plt.imshow(data2,aspect="auto",extent=[-ylim,ylim,-zlim,zlim]) 
    plt.xlabel("y [$\mu m$]")
    plt.ylabel("z [$\mu m$]")
    plt.show()
    plt.figure()
    plt.plot(x,data[int(len(z)/2),:]*1.47e-8)
    plt.ylabel("Optical dipole potential [Erec]")
    plt.ylim(0,1e-4)
    plt.show()
    print(data[int(len(z)/2),:])
    return data,data1,data2,x,y,z
